# Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
# Pan India Security — Workforce Management System

**Prepared For:** Pan India Securities Pvt Ltd  
**Website:** https://panindiasecurity.com  
**Version:** 1.0 | **Date:** 20 May 2026  

---

## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose
This SRS defines the complete functional and non-functional requirements for the **Pan India Security Workforce Management System** — a mobile-first platform to digitize and streamline security operations including guard management, GPS-based attendance, payroll, recruitment, and field inspections.

### 1.2 Intended Audience
Business Owners, Project Managers, Developers, UI/UX Designers, Backend Engineers, QA Engineers, Operations Team.

### 1.3 Key Definitions

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **Guard** | Security personnel deployed at client sites |
| **Site** | Client location where guards are posted |
| **Admin** | Single administrator with full system access |
| **Manager** | Field inspector responsible for site monitoring |
| **Recruiter** | Telecaller responsible for hiring candidates |
| **GeoFence** | GPS radius validation for attendance |
| **Payroll** | Salary calculation including deductions |

---

## 2. System Purpose & Objectives

### 2.1 Business Objectives
- Replace manual paper/Excel-based processes with a centralized digital platform
- Track guard attendance with GPS + selfie verification (prevent proxy attendance)
- Automate payroll with deductions (uniform, penalties, advances)
- Maintain centralized guard & recruitment databases
- Enable real-time site inspection reporting
- Improve operational transparency and reduce disputes

### 2.2 Technical Objectives
- Build a scalable React Native mobile app with role-based access
- Secure authentication via OTP + JWT
- Cloud-native backend with Supabase PostgreSQL
- Modular, maintainable architecture

---

## 3. Project Scope

### 3.1 In Scope
- Mobile workforce management (Android + iOS)
- **Single unified Admin** role (no super admin / ops admin split)
- Role-based authentication (4 roles)
- GPS + Selfie attendance system
- Site assignment & management
- Payroll with deductions
- Uniform tracking
- Recruitment pipeline management
- Field inspection & reporting
- Push notifications
- Document uploads
- Reporting dashboard

### 3.2 Out of Scope (Phase 1)
- Biometric hardware integration
- AI facial recognition
- Multi-language support
- Live GPS tracking (continuous)
- Advanced analytics / BI dashboard
- Client billing automation
- WhatsApp integration

